The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, September 15, 2003  Calcutta Column
				 																																									Private buses on route 3C/1 are very convenient for elderly people from north Calcutta to visit the Kalighat temple. A number of senior citizens of Dum Dum, Lake Town, Bangur Avenue and Shyamnagar Road will benefit if such a bus route is introduced till Dakshineswar.				 																																									B.N. Bose,				 																																									Dum Dum Park.				 																																									Earlier, All India Radio used to air a string of Durga Puja-related programmes, which used to usher in the festive mood. The programmes had a loyal band of listeners, but the authorities discontinued the practice for some unknown reasons. Cant it be revived?				 																																									Rabindranath Kar,				 																																									Sankar Ghosh Lane.
